WEBVTT

00:04.738 --> 00:06.505
Walter:
<i>My name is walter o'brien.</i>

00:06.507 --> 00:10.743
<i>I have the fourth highest iq</i>
<i>ever recorded: 197.</i>

00:10.745 --> 00:12.578
<i>Einstein's was 160.</i>

00:12.580 --> 00:15.180
<i>When I was 11, the fbi</i>
<i>arrested me for hacking nasa</i>

00:15.182 --> 00:17.616
<i>To get their blueprints</i>
<i>for my bedroom wall.</i>

00:17.618 --> 00:20.019
<i>Now I run a team of geniuses,</i>

00:20.021 --> 00:22.721
<i>Tackling worldwide threats</i>
<i>only we can solve.</i>

00:22.723 --> 00:24.656
<i>Toby's our behaviorist.</i>

00:24.658 --> 00:26.492
Sylvester's a human calculator.

00:26.494 --> 00:28.660
<i>Happy, a mechanical prodigy.</i>

00:28.662 --> 00:31.196
<i>Agent cabe gallo's</i>
<i>our government handler.</i>

00:31.198 --> 00:33.365
<i>And paige?</i>
<i>Well, paige isn't like us.</i>

00:33.367 --> 00:35.701
<i>She's normal</i>
<i>and translates the world for us</i>

00:35.703 --> 00:38.404
<i>While we help her understand</i>
<i>her genius son.</i>

00:38.406 --> 00:40.372
<i>Together, we are scorpion.</i>

00:41.608 --> 00:43.375
(news theme playing)

00:45.311 --> 00:47.679
The tranquil landscapes
often praised here in belarus

00:47.681 --> 00:51.083
May soon give way to rolling
tanks and blasting mortars

00:51.085 --> 00:53.786
As the century-long
border conflict with neighbors

00:53.788 --> 00:56.789
<i>Lithuania and latvia</i>
<i>has reignited.</i>

00:56.791 --> 00:59.324
With each nation being pledged
military support

00:59.326 --> 01:04.096
By respective allies,
russia, china, poland, germany,

01:04.098 --> 01:07.099
And the u.S.,
geopolitical experts fear

01:07.101 --> 01:09.435
If a resolution
is not reached quickly,

01:09.437 --> 01:12.404
All these countries
may soon be at war.

01:12.406 --> 01:13.405
Flight 5-19,

01:13.407 --> 01:15.808
Lax runway bravo is clear.

01:15.810 --> 01:18.410
Wind's one niner niner at two.

01:18.412 --> 01:20.712
Permission to land.

01:24.417 --> 01:25.751
Got an unregistered bogey, sir.

01:27.187 --> 01:30.189
It's only 500 feet
below a 747 heading eastbound.

01:31.758 --> 01:33.459
Establish contact immediately.

01:33.461 --> 01:35.194
The hell?

01:35.196 --> 01:36.795
It just... Vanished.

01:36.797 --> 01:38.497
Sylvester:
<i>I'm pretty sure</i>

01:38.499 --> 01:40.232
I just committed
at least three felonies.

01:40.234 --> 01:41.700
And I've seen <i>shawshank.</i>

01:41.702 --> 01:44.570
I know what they do to guys
like me in the big house.

01:44.572 --> 01:45.871
D block prom queen.

01:45.873 --> 01:47.706
That's it? It's gone?
It's still there.

01:47.708 --> 01:51.410
So it blends in with the
background of the atc monitor.

01:51.412 --> 01:52.644
Basically,
I made it disappear.

01:52.646 --> 01:55.848
That's lithuanian for
"sayonara," which is japanese

01:55.850 --> 01:57.282
For "good-bye."

01:57.284 --> 01:58.750
That plane will be
effectively invisible

01:58.752 --> 02:00.419
When it lands
at your private airstrip.

02:00.421 --> 02:02.488
I am still feeling
very uncomfortable with this.

02:02.490 --> 02:03.555
It's deceptive.

02:03.557 --> 02:05.190
Merrick:
Tensions are extremely high.

02:05.192 --> 02:07.392
If the world knew that the
leaders from belarus, lithuania,

02:07.394 --> 02:09.661
And latvia were flying
to the u.S.

02:09.663 --> 02:12.197
And no treaty was reached,
it could tip the entire region

02:12.199 --> 02:13.832
Over the edge.
I understand.

02:13.834 --> 02:15.834
But historically, when
governments try to hide facts

02:15.836 --> 02:18.770
From citizenry,
everyone winds up in hot water.

02:22.742 --> 02:24.810
(engine revving in distance)

02:37.323 --> 02:38.590
Paige:
Oh.

02:38.592 --> 02:40.859
You're still playing
with your toy?

02:40.861 --> 02:44.396
This toy is three-dimensional

02:44.398 --> 02:46.398
Viz-surround
software technology.

02:46.400 --> 02:47.633
Oh, it's-it's green screen.

02:47.635 --> 02:51.470
Wrong. It can be used
on a green screen,

02:51.472 --> 02:54.406
But my software allows you
to take various images

02:54.408 --> 02:57.609
From different sources
and layer them seamlessly

02:57.611 --> 02:59.211
On top of each other.

02:59.213 --> 03:00.712
Like colorforms.

03:00.714 --> 03:01.914
The kids' toy.

03:01.916 --> 03:04.383
I didn't play with
kids' toys. Anyway,

03:04.385 --> 03:05.918
Even fbi video forensics

03:05.920 --> 03:08.253
Couldn't detect these images
as fake.

03:08.255 --> 03:10.322
They're groundbreaking.
Good. Because

03:10.324 --> 03:11.790
You're gonna need to fool a lot
of people today.

03:11.792 --> 03:13.592
Oh, it will.
So, speaking of today,

03:13.594 --> 03:14.760
Did you see my analysis report?

03:14.762 --> 03:16.828
Uh, yeah.
Okay. I know what you're doing,

03:16.830 --> 03:19.531
So let me be more specific.
Did you read my report?

03:20.900 --> 03:22.768
Come on. 25 pages

03:22.770 --> 03:24.770
Detailing the customs and
history of the three countries

03:24.772 --> 03:25.871
Who are meeting today.

03:25.873 --> 03:27.539
It's important.

03:27.541 --> 03:29.942
I understand.
But, uh, so is this,

03:29.944 --> 03:31.610
And I just didn't
get around to it.

03:31.612 --> 03:32.945
Uh, why did you write it anyway?

03:32.947 --> 03:35.781
I never asked you to.
Well, truth is,

03:35.783 --> 03:38.517
I'm taking night classes.
One's on european history.

03:38.519 --> 03:41.720
Had a paper due. We had this
case coming up, so, you know,

03:41.722 --> 03:43.555
I figured two birds,
one stone.

03:43.557 --> 03:45.924
You dropped out of college.

03:45.926 --> 03:49.361
I re-enrolled
to finish my degree, yeah.

03:49.363 --> 03:50.562
Uh-huh. Why?
To learn,

03:50.564 --> 03:51.897
For the betterment
of myself,

03:51.899 --> 03:54.266
And to set a good example
for ralph.
I get that.

03:54.268 --> 03:56.268
It's great
that you're pursuing education,

03:56.270 --> 03:58.804
But why european history?

03:58.806 --> 04:01.240
Liberal arts
are complete nonsense.

04:01.242 --> 04:02.908
Oh, I couldn't disagree more.

04:02.910 --> 04:04.977
The information that you receive
is strictly dependent

04:04.979 --> 04:08.547
On the beliefs of whoever
authored the textbooks.

04:08.549 --> 04:12.451
There are only four subjects
worth studying: Science and math

04:12.453 --> 04:13.919
And math and science.
Okay,

04:13.921 --> 04:16.989
So when you meet the lithuanian
president, what will you do?

04:16.991 --> 04:19.925
I'll say hello
and shake his hand.
Mm-hmm.

04:19.927 --> 04:21.827
And that could be disastrous
because when you shake the hands

04:21.829 --> 04:23.962
Of a lithuanian in the
threshold of a room,

04:23.964 --> 04:25.864
It's considered insulting.

04:25.866 --> 04:28.734
If the fate of civilization
rests on where we shake hands

04:28.736 --> 04:31.803
With these people,
then we're all doomed.

04:38.878 --> 04:40.979
(horses neighing over video)

04:43.916 --> 04:46.318
Hey, hopalong.

04:46.320 --> 04:47.953
We're about to hop along,
so why don't you stop

04:47.955 --> 04:50.856
Watching that movie
for the 12th time?

04:50.858 --> 04:52.858
This movie was filmed
on the senator's compound

04:52.860 --> 04:54.826
Where the summit's taking place.

04:54.828 --> 04:56.728
I'm studying the layout
of the grounds

04:56.730 --> 04:59.064
'cause some of the sets are
still standing on the property.

04:59.066 --> 05:01.066
You already walked the
ground with homeland.

05:01.068 --> 05:02.968
You're a fanboy.

05:04.904 --> 05:07.572
Next time, let your horse do
the thinking.

05:07.574 --> 05:09.508
He's smarter.

05:09.510 --> 05:12.544
They don't make classics
like this anymore.

05:13.613 --> 05:15.480
Fanboy.

05:16.783 --> 05:18.417
Hey, you got
a second?

05:18.419 --> 05:19.551
What are you doing?

05:19.553 --> 05:20.552
With what?

05:20.554 --> 05:21.720
Hand, back.

05:21.722 --> 05:23.588
Yours, mine.
Oh.

05:23.590 --> 05:25.824
Sorry, I didn't
even notice.

05:25.826 --> 05:28.560
Happy: Yesterday, you brushed
a leaf from my hair,

05:28.562 --> 05:30.362
And on Tuesday
you laughed hysterically

05:30.364 --> 05:31.630
At something I said.

05:31.632 --> 05:32.898
How do you know
it wasn't funny?

05:32.900 --> 05:34.466
I was reading a menu.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.468
Pupu platter?

05:36.470 --> 05:39.371
I can't help but feel
something's changed.

05:39.373 --> 05:40.872
Are you referring to our kiss?
Don't...

05:40.874 --> 05:41.973
Say it.

05:41.975 --> 05:43.542
(whispers):
Kiss.

05:43.544 --> 05:45.677
Almost kiss.

05:45.679 --> 05:48.847
It didn't happen.

05:50.850 --> 05:52.851
Yet.

05:52.853 --> 05:54.920
(helicopter whirring)

06:04.831 --> 06:06.832
Cabe:
That's lithuanian president

06:06.834 --> 06:10.936
Dmitri kreshenko and
his chief advisor mikko aleska.

06:10.938 --> 06:13.105
Merrick: Over there is
belarus president

06:13.107 --> 06:14.406
Boris sakovich

06:14.408 --> 06:15.974
And his entourage,

06:15.976 --> 06:19.778
And finally
latvian president juris nikonov.

06:19.780 --> 06:24.383
Their president's more
of a figurehead.

06:24.385 --> 06:26.685
You didn't read
my report either.

06:26.687 --> 06:28.553
All right,
let's get to work.

06:28.555 --> 06:29.855
Woman:
Director merrick.

06:29.857 --> 06:31.490
Ah, ms. Munoz.

06:31.492 --> 06:32.824
Cabe, this is
renÃ© munoz,

06:32.826 --> 06:34.793
